column5: I was hoping to fire up the sled this weekend and hit the ice on my local lake but as you can see it obviously isn't safe as there are still large sections with free flowing water. Mother nature isn't cooperating.
Which body of water is this?

Looks like Holiday Pines to me. If it is, that is the mouth of the rive on the East end of Rice Lake. We used to have a cottage there, (Ashphedol Park). We went knee boarding on New Years Day a few moons ago in that area.
Way to go RON, you are correct. Pic is taken from the south shore of Rice Lake in the Roseneath area. Not sure what across from me, but again, you are probably correct.
